body:
We've designed the API to throw 422 (missing parameters) errors when required parameters are missing. However, it looks like the production environment is throwing 500 (internal server) errors when we're trying to throw 422 errors. This is problematic in that it makes user errors look like API bugs and time-consuming to diagnose.

Locally, this throws a 422 for missing district but throws a 500 on the server: 

500 error:
https://api.open.fec.gov/v1/elections/?API_KEY=DEMO_KEY

422 error:
http://localhost:5000/v1/elections/

```
{
message: {
cycle: [
"Missing data for required field."
],
office: [
"Missing data for required field."
]
},
status: 422
}
```

We should make sure our develop/stage/production environment return the proper server errors.

@jmcarp:  @lindsay   

Candidate H6NY19169 (cmte id C00580415) isn't showing up with numbers. He should have numbers. I looked in the warehouse and he has filed a form 3 and his candidate id and committee id are linked.  
https://fec-proxy.18f.gov/data/candidate/H6NY19169/

Some candidate election years are either in the future or before the FEC existed. We can filter these candidates and/or years out of our views, but it would be helpful to get them cleaned up in the raw data if possible. Examples:

